<div>
<div>
<div><div>
<p>If you have a lot of content on Confluence, staying on top of everything may seem a little daunting. These tips will help you save time and track all the content you care about.</p>
</div></div><p> </p><p> </p></div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<h2 id="Stayontopofwhat&#39;simportanttoyou-MySpaces"><span><img height="184" width="280" src="https://templates.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/33386/My%20Spaces.png?api=v2"></span>My Spaces</h2><p>Add your favorite spaces, or ones you&#39;ll visit regularly, to your list of &#39;My Spaces&#39;. They appear on the Confluence dashboard, so you&#39;ve got quick access to them. You can also use the <a href="https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/ConfCloud/Spaces+List+Macro" rel="nofollow">Spaces List Macro</a> to display them on a page.</p><p>To add a space to your list of &#39;My Spaces&#39;, navigate to it and hit the <strong>star icon</strong> next to the Space Name.</p><p> </p><h2 id="Stayontopofwhat&#39;simportanttoyou-Saveforlater">Save for later</h2><p>If it&#39;s a page or blog post you need quick access to, rather than a whole space, hit <strong>Save for later </strong>and it&#39;ll be in <strong>My Work</strong> on your dashboard. You can even use the <a href="https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/ConfCloud/Favorite+Pages+Macro" rel="nofollow">Favorite Pages Macro</a> to display a list of all of everything you&#39;ve saved for later.</p><p><span><img height="41" width="422" src="https://templates.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/33386/page%20menu.png?api=v2"></span></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p></div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p> </p><p> </p></div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<h2 id="Stayontopofwhat&#39;simportanttoyou-@mentions">@mentions</h2><p>Use @mentions whenever you want someone&#39;s input. Mention a teammate, and they&#39;ll get a notification with a link to the page, post, or comment. Mention someone when <a href="https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/ConfCloud/Add%2C+Assign%2C+and+View+Tasks" rel="nofollow">creating a task</a>, and the task is assigned to them. Find all your assigned tasks in your profile.</p><p>Mentions are a great alternative to email. If you want someone to look something over, add additional information, or approve anything, assign it to them as a task. They can make any changes or comment in Confluence. They may even let you know they&#39;re done by mentioning you back <img src="https://templates.atlassian.net/wiki/s/1010156557/6452/6d00854cb08a28dc5d19c9438d4db4ac90d8e011/_/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png" width="16" height="16" alt="(wink)"/></p><p> </p><h2 id="Stayontopofwhat&#39;simportanttoyou-Watchapage,blogorspace"><span><img height="193" width="300" src="https://templates.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/33386/watch%20page.png?api=v2"></span>Watch a page, blog or space</h2><p>Keep track of changes made to a page, post, or space by <a href="https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/ConfCloud/Watch+Pages%2C+Spaces+and+Blogs" rel="nofollow">watching</a> it.</p><p>Watching something means you&#39;ll get an email notification when there&#39;s an edit, a comment, or a new attachment.</p><p>When you watch a space, you&#39;re also notified when pages are created or deleted in the space.</p><ul><li>To watch a page, go to the page and choose <strong>Watch</strong> &gt; <strong>Watch page</strong>. To watch the whole space, choose <strong>Watch all content in this space</strong>.</li><li>To watch a blog, navigate to that blog and choose <strong>Watch this blog.</strong></li></ul><p>You can manage watchers for any space you&#39;re an admin of. It&#39;s useful when you&#39;re creating a new project and want team members to track its progress.</p><p>Go to any page in the space and choose <strong>Watch </strong>&gt; <strong>Manage Watchers,</strong> then add or delete any names under &#39;Watching this space&#39;.</p></div>
</div>
